### @name login
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "instructor@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Grab the token from the login response
@token = {{login.response.body.token}}

### -------------------------------------------

### @name createCourse
POST http://localhost:5000/api/courses
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "title": "Advanced Node.js",
  "description": "A course created with REST Client.",
  "category": "Web Development",
  "price": 120
}

### Grab the courseId from the create course response
@courseId = {{createCourse.response.body.data._id}}

### -------------------------------------------

### @name addLecture
POST http://localhost:5000/api/courses/{{courseId}}/lectures
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "title": "Chapter 5: Advanced Middleware",
  "content": "This is the content for the new lecture."
}